Winget: 
How to call as administrator 

[gets the path that winget.exe resides in] 

$WingetDir = Get-Childitem -Path "C:\Program Files\WindowsApps\Microsoft.DesktopAppInstaller*" -Include winget.exe -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -Last 1 | %{$_.FullName} | Split-Path  


This was a precise path for the winget on a machine that the top command did not work for: 

C:\Program Files\WindowsApps\Microsoft.DesktopAppInstaller_1.25.340.0_x64__8wekyb3d8bbwe 

[changes to directory that winget resides in] 

cd $WingetDir 

 

Then run .\winget.exe out of there 

  

 To update all apps (sounds good, but may not be good idea based on company deployment methods): 
.\winget.exe update --all --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

  

To update Adobe CreativeCloud only: 

.\winget.exe update --id=Adobe.CreativeCloud -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

To update Adobe Acrobat only: 

.\winget.exe update --id=Adobe.Acrobat.Reader.64-bit -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

To update Dell Command Update only: 

.\winget.exe update --id=Dell.CommandUpdate.Universal -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

To update MS Edge only: 

.\winget.exe update --id= Microsoft.Edge -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements  

To update MS Office only: 
.\winget.exe update --id=Microsoft.Office -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

 

To update Notepad++ only: 

.\winget.exe update --id=Notepad++.Notepad++ -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

To update Docker only: 

.\winget.exe update --id=Docker.DockerDesktop -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

To update Adobe Illustrator only: 

.\winget.exe update --id=ARP\Machine\X86\ILST_30_1 -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

To update Mozilla Firefox only: 

.\winget.exe update --id=Mozilla.Firefox -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

To update Java JRE only: 

.\winget.exe update --id=Oracle.JavaRuntimeEnvironment -e --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements 

 

Explanation: 

winget install – Tells Windows Package Manager to install a package. 

--id=Adobe.CreativeCloud – Specifies the exact package ID for Adobe Creative Cloud from the winget repository. 

-e – Ensures an exact match on the package ID to avoid installing the wrong application. 

 

If you get an error when trying to update an app like this: 

image.pngRun this command 

.\winget settings --enable BypassCertificatePinningForMicrosoftStore 

 

 Then try the update command again 

 

